         <abstract>
            <p>A computational procedure based on linear programming is presented for finding the best one-sided L&lt;sub&gt;1&lt;/sub&gt; approximation to a given function. A theorem which ensures that the computational procedure yields approximations which converge to the best approximation is proved. Some numerical examples are discussed.</p>
          </abstract>
